INSERT [dbo].[FAQ] ([FAQ_Id], [Category], [Title], [Contents], [File_Name], [DisplayOrder], [Status], [Created_Date], [Created_By], [Modified_Date], [Modified_By]) VALUES (2, 7002, N'Legal FAQ', N'<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>What documents are needed, if your parents are coming to you in the US?<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>From the co’s side you may require an employment verification letter stating your parent’s names and your current employment details with us.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>If your H1B approval gives you dates of validity much beyond the total of 6 years of stay on L & H status, should you inform the USCIS and file for extension prior to the expiry date or file later as if the approval is correct. <o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>Such errors are common with the USCIS where H1B approvals from them do not count the previous stays on H & L status and current approvals authorize stay much beyond what they actually should have authorized. In such cases, it’s advisable to not wait for the H1B to expire as per the approval received but file in time as per your own calculation as to when the total of 6 years on H & L status should be expiring. Though there is nothing wrong in staying in the US till the time authorized by the USCIS on I-129 approval, but in case there is an error on the USCIS it’s your duty to have it rectified as at any later point of time if that error is found out by the USCIS, there is chance of being penalized.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>Is it necessary to go to their home country for stamping in case of H1b transfer or extension?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>Visa stamping is only required to enter the US. If you are staying and working within the US you do not necessarily require your H1B transfer or extension to be stamped on your passport. You only need the visa to re-enter the US. In case you have a visa already stamped on your passport , from your previous employer, which has not yet expired, you may still use it along with our co’s I-129 approval. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><o:p><FONT face=Calibri size=3> </FONT></o:p></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>Can I check the status of my USCIS filings online?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>USCIS filing status can be checked online at the USCIS website uscis.gov. You ‘ll require your EAC# handy for that. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><o:p><FONT face=Calibri size=3> </FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>How can I update my address with USCIS?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>You can file the AR-11 online at the USCIS website and have your address updated in the USCIS records for your pending appellations and even otherwise. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><o:p><FONT face=Calibri size=3> </FONT></o:p></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>How soon can I file for renewal of H1B?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>The earliest H1B renewal can be filed is 6 months prior to the expiry date. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><o:p><FONT face=Calibri size=3> </FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>What are the steps to filing a green card?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>Green Card filing generally involves 3 steps:-</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"><FONT size=3>·</FONT><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt Times New Roman">         </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT face=Calibri size=3>Labor filing</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"><FONT size=3>·</FONT><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt Times New Roman">         </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT face=Calibri size=3>I-140 – Petition for Immigrant Worker </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoListParagraphCxSpLast style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"><FONT size=3>·</FONT><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt Times New Roman">         </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT face=Calibri size=3>I-485 – Application for Adjustment of Status</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>What is a LCA?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>Labor condition application or LCA is a legal requirement to be filed with the Department of Labor when we file your H1B application. While we file the LCA at that time we also acknowledge that in case your work location changes from NJ to some city state outside the state of NJ we shall file a fresh LCA for that location. Hence each time you start a project outside the state of NJ the Legal department at Compunnel files a fresh LCA for you for each different county that you work in. A copy of that LCA is provided to you for your reference after filing. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>How does one get Labor filed and what all is required for it?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>For Labor filing you need to have a 4 years Bachelors degree or 4+2 years Masters degree in Computers Science or related field plus atleast 4 yrs/1yr work experience documented in detailed experience letters from past employers. To initiate the Labor process you need to download the Labor package available in the Compunnel portal under Forms/Legal fill and send to us along with your latest I-94 & visa copy and experience letters from past employers.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>What are the categories under which Compunnel can file Labor for me under?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>Labor through Compunnel can be filed under 2 categories- EB2 & EB3. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>How long does Labor certification take?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>Labor certification may take from few weeks to a few months time, it depends on case to case. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>What is processing time for I-140 approval?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>I-140 approval may take anywhere from 6 months to over an year to get approved. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>What is priority date?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>The day your Labor is filed is locked as your Priority date. The movement of your application at the I-485 stage is dependent on your Priority date. The older the Priority date the faster your GC will get approved. You may check whether your priority date is current or not with eth USCIS visa bulletin that get updated every month. The link is </FONT><A href="http://travel.state.gov/visa/frvi/bulletin/bulletin_1360.html"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>http://travel.state.gov/visa/frvi/bulletin/bulletin_1360.html</FONT></A><FONT face=Calibri size=3>. Here you can check the current month’s and the previous months visa bulletins.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><o:p><FONT face=Calibri size=3> </FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>Can I check my Labor application status online?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>Labor application status can be checked online at the Department of Labor (DoL) website but with the Employers’ log in ID and password. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>What happens after Labor is certified?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>After Labor is certified we file the I-140 or the Petition for Immigrant Worker. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>How long does I-140 process take?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>I-140 approval takes roughly 6 months to 1year to get approved. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>When can I file the I-485?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>I-485 can be filed when your priority date (date when your Labor is filed) becomes current. Becoming current here means that when your PD shows on the travel visa bulletin of the USCIS under your country and your category. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>What all is required for filing the I-485?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>The list of docs required for I-485 filing is available at Compunnel portal/Legal/Legal documents and filing procedures.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>How long does I-485 process take?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>I-485 process may take a few months to a few years to get approved depending which country you belong to and how do the application move with the USCIS for that country and your category. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>What is the EAD and when can I file the EAD?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>EAD stands for Employment Authorization Document. When you reach the I-485 stage in your GC process, the USCIS allows you an alternate work authorization to work in the US with. EAD is an option that allows you work in the US for any employer not limiting to your initial H1B sponsoring employer.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>How soon can I file for renewal of EAD/AP?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>The earliest EAD/AP renewals<B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"> </B>can be filed is 120 days from the date of expiry.<B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"> <o:p></o:p></B></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>Is it mandatory to file for EAD/AP once I file for I-485?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>EAD/AP filing is not mandatory with the I-485 filing. You can file both or either if you require a work authorization document or a travel document, respectively. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>Can I maintain my H1B status after my I-485 is filed?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>Yes H1B can be maintained after filing I-485. You need to keep filing for your H1B extensions on time and continue to earn minimum H1B salary. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>Is it mandatory to extend the H1B after the I-485 is filed?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>No it is not mandatory to extend your H1B after you file your I-485, as you have the option of filing EAD in order to work in the US. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>Can I file EAD/AP online?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>Yes EAD/AP can be filed online. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>Where can I know the documentary requirements for various USCIS filings and their related fees?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>You may visit the Compunnel portal and go to Legal/Legal Documents and Filing Procedures to know the documentary requirements and applicable USCIS for various relevant USCIS filings. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>How and when can I add my spouse to my already filed I-485?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </SPAN>Your spouse can be added to your I-485 application if she has entered the US on dependant – H-4 status<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </SPAN>and your priority dates are current in the USCIS bulletin. </FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>If Labor is denied is there any waiting time period to file another one?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>If Labor is denied, refilling can be done immediately, provided we have the advertisements current. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Calibri>Can we go outside US after I-140 Filing?<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><FONT face=Calibri size=3>Yes, travel after I-140 filing is not forbidden.</FONT></P>
